t is what usually happens. It is sort of plural, but not split.</i> (Ian White) <br><br>A screening of five videos by six artists from London: Lucy Clout, Manuela Gernedel & Morag Keil, Gil Leung, Rachel Reupke, and James Richards. Introduced by Jamie Stevens. <br><br><br>///Screening starts at 7.15pm<br>Doors at 6.45pm ',NULL),(93,1,'2014-07-29 23:12:18','2021-06-10 15:45:19',70,'Our Program',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'our-program',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								',_binary '\r\n																								\r\n																								<br>																								On view:<br><br><i>January 20 - June 30, 2021</i>:<br>The 2020-2021 Capp Street Artist-in-Residence is <a href=\"/gallery/raven-chacon-radio-coyote\">Raven Chacon</a>.<br><br><i>May 9 - June 6, 2021</i>:<br>CCA’s Graduate Program in Curatorial Practice Class of 2021 present <a href=\"/gallery/contact-traces-2021\"><i>Contact Traces</i></a><br><br><i>September 9 - December 4, 2021</i>:<br><i>Long Kwento</i> features new paintings and sculptures by <a href=\"/gallery/maia-cruz-palileo-long-kwento-2021\">Maia Cruz Palileo</a>.<br><br>(read more about our exhibition program <a href=\"/read-about-us/the-exhibition-program\">here</a>)<br><br>///On our mind:<br><br><i>September 2020 - July 2021</i>:<br><a href=\"/on-our-mind/cecilia-vicua-a-is-on-our-mind-2020-2021\">Cecilia Vicuña</a> is on our mind.<br><br>(read more about our research seasons <a href=\"/read-about-us/the-research-seasons\">here</a>)',_binary '\r\n																								\r\n																								\r\n																								'),(94,1,'2014-07-31 05:47:08','2014-07-31 05:47:08',90,'_Emails',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'emails',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(95,1,'2014-07-31 05:47:38','2014-07-31 05:47:38',10,'News',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'news',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(96,1,'2014-07-31 05:48:04','2021-06-08 21:40:04',20,'Emails',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'emails',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '\r\n																								\r\n																								',_binary '<br>																								<br>																								',_binary '\r\n																								\r\n																								'),(97,1,'2014-07-31 05:48:14','2014-09-24 18:41:10',30,'Exhibitions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'exhibitions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(98,1,'2014-07-31 05:48:25','2014-07-31 05:48:25',40,'Limited Editions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'limited-editions',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(99,1,'2014-07-31 05:48:35','2014-09-24 18:40:47',50,'Members',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'members',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(100,1,'2014-07-31 05:48:46','2014-07-31 22:56:09',70,'Curators Forum',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'curators-forum',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(101,1,'2014-07-31 05:49:03','2014-07-31 05:49:03',70,'Notes from the Field',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'notes-from-the-field',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(102,1,'2014-07-31 05:52:34','2015-01-10 02:48:15',1,'_Template',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'template',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<a href=\'http://wattis.org/\'>CCA Wattis Institute</a><br> Director Anthony Huberman<br>invites you and a guest to celebrate the opening of two new exhibitions:<br><br><a href=\'/gallery/jos-de-gruyter-harald-thys-tram-3-2015\'>Jos de Gruyter & Harald Thys</a><br>(a solo show of new and recent work)<br><br><a href=\'/apartment/nairy-baghramian-off-broadway-2015\'>Off Broadway</a> <br>(a group show organized by the artist Nairy Baghramian)<br><br><span style=\"color:#ff0000\">VIP reception<br>Wed<span style=\"color:#ff0000\">/</span>January 21, 2015<br>5:30-7pm<br>6pm Introduction</span><br><br>CCA Wattis Institute<br>350 Kansas St. (16th St.)<br>San Francisco<br><br>RSVP by 1.16/2015 to <a href=\'mailto:rsvp@cca.edu\'>rsvp@cca.edu</a>  or [510] 594-3604.',_binary '<i>Jos de Gruyter and Harald Thys</i> is made possibly by the government of Flanders, Belgium through Flanders House New York, with special thanks to Isabella Bortolozzi Galerie and Galerie Micheline Szwajcer. <i>Off Broadway</i> is made possible by the Institut für Auslandsbeziehungen and the Goethe-Institut San Francisco, with special thanks to Galerie Daniel Buchholz. The CCA Wattis Institute program is generously supported by the Andy Warhol Foundation for the Visual Arts, Grants for the Arts/San Francisco Hotel Tax Fund, and the Phyllis C. Wattis Foundation; by CCA Director’s Fund contributors Patricia W. Fitzpatrick, Judy and Bill Timken, Ruth and Alan Stein, Robin Wright and Ian Reeves, Laura Brugger and Ross Sappenfield; and by CCA’s Curator’s Forum. Phyllis C. Wattis was the generous founding patron. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(103,1,'2014-07-31 23:04:04','2014-08-13 09:05:56',NULL,'September 9, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'september-9-2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<br/><br/>\r\n<div class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">9.9/2014</div>',_binary '<a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/gallery/markus-schinwald-new-work-2014\'>Markus Schinwald</a> is in the gallery<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span> He is showing new work<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span><br><br><a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/apartment/nairy-baghramian-off-broadway-2015\'>Nairy Baghramian</a> is in the apartment<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span> For the next six months<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">,</span> she will invite other artists to participate<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span><br><br><a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/on-our-mind/joan-jonas-is-on-our-mind-2014-2015\'>Joan Jonas</a> is on our mind<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span> A year of events will reflect on her work<span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span><br><br>Oscar Tuazon has built a new <a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/gallery/markus-schinwald-new-work-2014\'>bar</a><span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">,</span><br><br>David Reinfurt has programmed a <a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/\'>new website</a><span class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.</span><br><br><div class=\"floatPad times big black animatePunctuation\">.+*</div><br><i>On Tuesday, September 9, </i><a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/main\'>The Wattis Institute</a> <i>for Contemporary Arts at California College of the Arts re-opens with a reception from 7–9 pm.</i><br><br>360 Kansas Street (16th St.)<br>San Francisco<br><a href=\'http://wattis-stage.cca.edu/\'>www.wattis.org</a><br><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"JS/animatePunctuation.js\"></script><br><script>initPunctuation(\'animatePunctuation\', 200, true);</script>',NULL),(104,1,'2014-07-31 23:13:36','2014-07-31 23:14:54',NULL,'September 12, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'september-12-2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<div id=\"Punct-1\" class=\"floatPad times big black\">:/} Event </div><script type=\"text/javascript\" src=\"JS/animatePunctuation.js\"></script><script>initPunctuation(\'Punct\', 200, true);</script>',_binary 'Arizona is home to Arizonans, but also to the Native American Hopi tribe. Every other summer, they perform the Hopi snake dance, which is believed to have the power to summon the rain.<br><br>Many might find it an irrational exercise, but Aby Warburg, among others, was impressed with the rigor, precision, and seriousness of the ritual--and how much it shares with Greek mythology and with Renaissance, no matter how unrelated those might seem at first glance.<br><br>Joan Jonas saw the dance in the 1960s, and it informed a 2006 performance she called \"The Shape, The Scent, The Feel of Things.\" In it, she uses bodies, props, sound, and video to tell a story about a story.<br><br>Professor Ann Reynolds, from the University of Texas at Austin, met Jonas in 2006. They have become close, and she is currently working on an essay for Jonas, to be published in the catalogue of the 2015 Venice Biennale, where Jonas will be representing the United States.<br><br>Dr. Reynolds begins our year dedicated to reflecting on the work of Joan Jonas with a lecture entitled XXXXXX.<br><br>Ann Reynolds on Joan Jonas<br>September 12, 2014<br>7pm<br><br>CCA Wattis Institute<br>360 Kansas Street<br>San Francisco',NULL),(105,1,'2014-07-31 23:43:46','2014-10-21 00:20:59',10,'_Template',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'template',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\'\'>Notes_From°the Field</a>“',_binary 'Ed Atkins (British, b. 1982) has exhibited widely and internationally in the past few years, moving from early exercises in digital structuralism to his more recent, decidedly textual, organization of perversely real CGI animations. Behind all his works is a version of the artist himself, often presented in crisis, with a punctured self-reflexivity that nevertheless vitalizes and exceeds its powerfully apparent artifice. Since his exhibition at Chisenhale Gallery, London (2012), one consistently deployed visual motif has been a high-resolution animation of his own head, often decapitated, highlighting the process of abstraction between artistic labour and the delivered and mediated artistic self. An important and under-valued component in Atkins’ videos and performances is his careful design of sound, in which he evens out unlikely influences — from Baroque choral music to contemporary improvisation — into hissing sonic surfaces that push his texts into spaces beyond the spoken word.<br><br>Atkins’ exhibition at Mainz features a number of recent works, including his most recent video Ribbons, which was co-commissioned by Kunsthalle Zurich and The Serpentine, London, where Atkins staged exhibitions earlier this year. Having followed Atkins’ work for a long period (since his MA exhibition at the Slade School of Art in 2009), I believe that this recent trio of exhibitions marks a high point in his work to date: essayistic long-form videos are combined with shorter animations — for instance, a looped animation of his own bloodied head rolling down a stairwell — as well as ink drawings mounted on architectural panels, and multi-channel sound installations. Atkins can be considered to be one of the most celebrated young artists working today, and as the scale and status of his institutional collaborators increases, his work adapts in the best possible ways, all the while retaining his skepticism and seriousness.<br><br>His exhibition in Mainz continues until 28 September 2014. <br><br>— <i>Jamie Stevens</i><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>',NULL),(106,1,'2014-08-02 01:34:47','2014-08-02 01:34:47',NULL,'Untitled',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'untitled',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','',NULL),(107,1,'2014-08-02 02:19:19','2016-12-26 21:10:21',499,'Saturday, September 13, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'saturday-september-13-2014',NULL,'2014-09-13 15:00:00','2014-09-13 17:00:00',NULL,NULL,_binary '. . . Ann Reynolds talks about Joan Jonas.',_binary 'Professor <a href=\'http://www.utexas.edu/finearts/aah/about/people/ann-reynolds\' target=\'new\'>Ann Reynolds</a>, from the University of Texas at Austin, met Joan Jonas in 2006. They are both interested in Aby Warburg, the Hopi Rain Dance, and using bodies, props, sound, and video to tell a story about a story.<br><br>Reynolds is currently working on an essay for Jonas, to be published in the catalogue of the 2015 Venice Biennale, where Jonas will be representing the United States.<br><br>This event is organized by <a href=\"\">Anthony Huberman</a> and is the first of a year-long series of events about and around the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/joan-jonas-is-on-our-mind-2014-2015\">Joan Jonas</a>.<br><br><br>///The lecture begins at 3pm<br><br>P.S.: since Prof. Reynolds\'s lecture is based on her unpublished essay for the 2015 Venice Biennale, she understandably asked that we not post a recording of the event online.',NULL),(108,1,'2014-08-07 00:21:30','2016-12-26 21:09:45',497,'Wednesday, October 1, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'wednesday-october-1-2014',NULL,'2014-10-01 19:00:00','2014-10-01 21:00:00',NULL,NULL,_binary '. . . Alex Waterman and Will Holder launch their book about Robert Ashley.',_binary 'An event to launch <i>Yes, But Is It Edible?</i>, a publication of new typographical scores derived from the notations of composer Robert Ashley (1930-2014). <br><br><br>Over the past four years, Will Holder and Alex Waterman, the book\'s editors, have been reading \'duets\' in order to produce and test new scores. For this event, Holder and Waterman give a public reading one final time before handing the work over to others.<br><br><br><br>///Reading starts at 7.15pm<br>Doors at 6.45pm<br><br>P.S. Buy the book <a href = \'http://new-documents.org/books/yes-but-is-it-edible\' target= \'new\'>here</a>. ',NULL),(109,1,'2014-08-07 00:23:29','2016-12-26 21:09:34',496,'Thursday, October 9, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'thursday-october-9-2014',NULL,'2014-10-09 19:00:00','2014-10-09 21:00:00',NULL,NULL,_binary '. . . Joan Jonas gives a lecture about poetry and politics.',_binary 'Joan Jonas is <a href=\"/on-our-mind/joan-jonas-is-on-our-mind-2014-2015\">on our mind</a>. She gives a lecture about poetry and politics.<br><br>Joan Jonas (b. 1936 in New York) is a pioneer of video and performance art; her early work from the 1960s and 1970s anticipated the following forty years of multimedia. <br><br>This is the second of a year-long series of events about the work of <a href=\"http://www.wattis.org//on-our-mind/joan-jonas-is-on-our-mind-2014-2015\">Joan Jonas</a>.<br><br><br>///Talk begins at 7pm<br>Doors open at 6.30pm<br><br>P.S. A video of the lecture is below.<br>',_binary '<iframe src=\"//player.vimeo.com/video/111051709?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe>'),(110,1,'2014-08-07 00:25:22','2016-12-26 21:09:10',494,'Thursday, October 30, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'thursday-october-30-2014',NULL,'2014-10-30 19:15:00','2014-10-30 22:15:00',NULL,NULL,_binary '. . . Steve Kado on Terry Riley.',_binary 'Steve Kado gives a performance about the work of minimalist composer Terry Riley. <br><br>Kado is <a href=\"http://theblankket.com\" target=\"new\">an artist and musician</a> who lives between Toronto and Los Angeles. <br><br>This is our attempt to mark <a href=\"http://www.wqxr.org/story/136432-november-4-1964-the-premiere-of-terry-rileys-in-c/\" target=\"new\">the 50th anniversary</a> of Riley\'s landmark musical piece <i>In C</i>, which was first performed at the San Francisco Tape Music Center. <br><br><a href=\'calendar\'><</a>///Doors at 6.45 pm<br>Performance begins at 7.15 pm',_binary '<iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/124673354\" width=\"500\" height=\"281\" frameborder=\"0\" webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen allowfullscreen></iframe> '),(111,1,'2014-08-07 00:26:16','2016-12-26 21:10:33',500,'Tuesday, September 9, 2014',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'tuesday-september-9-2014',NULL,'2014-09-09 19:00:00','2014-09-09 21:00:00',NULL,NULL,_binary '. . . Beneath’s record <i>Vobes</i> plays in our new event space.',_binary 'To coincide with the reopening of the Wattis Institute, Beneath’s EP <i>Vobes</i> plays throughout the evening in our new event space.<br><br>This record was released by <a href=\'http://p-a-n.org\' target=\'new\'>PAN</a>.<br><br><br>///7-9pm <br><br>',''),(112,1,'2014-08-07 00:54:44','2018-12-17 01:51:39',10,'Past exhibitions (2014 â€“ present) . . . ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'past-exhibitions-2014-a-present',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'All exhibitions beginning in 2014 are available here.///',NULL),(113,1,'2014-08-07 00:55:12','2015-06-16 22:03:30',20,'2014 â€“ (events) . . . ',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2014-a-events',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'All events beginning in 2014 are available here.///',NULL),(114,1,'2014-08-07 01:23:02','2021-01-26 00:31:07',10,'Capp Street Artists (1984 â€“ )',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'capp-street-artists-1984-a',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Since its inception, Capp Street Project has given more than 100 local, national, and international artists the opportunity to create new work through its residency and public exhibition programs.',_binary '2020-2021<br><a href=\"/gallery/raven-chacon-radio-coyote\">Raven Chacon</a><br><br>2019-2020<br><a href=\"/gallery/ha-ng-a-n-tr%C3%A6-%C3%A6-ng-we-listen-nearby-2020\">Hồng-Ân Trương</a><br><br>2018-2019<br><a href=\"/gallery/abbas-akhavan-cast-for-a-folly-2019\">Abbas Akhavan</a><br><br>2017-2018<br><a href=\"/gallery/contemptorary-deep-time-construction-2018\">contemptorary</a><br><br>2016-2017<br><a href=\"/gallery/melanie-gilligan-parts-wholes-2016\">Melanie Gilligan</a><br><br>2015-2016<br><a href=\"/gallery/carissa-rodriguez-i-m-normal-i-have-a-garden-i-m-a-person-2015\">Carissa Rodriguez</a><br><br>2014-2015<br><a href=\"/apartment/nairy-baghramian-off-broadway-2015\">Nairy Baghramian</a><br><br>2013-2014<br><a href=\"http://archive.wattis.org/exhibitions/claire-fontaine\" target=\'new\'>Claire Fontaine</a><br><br>2012-2013<br><a href=\"http://archive.wattis.org/exhibitions/magnificent-seven-ryan-gander\" target=\'new\'>Ryan Gander</a><br><br>2011-2012<br><a hr