07-27 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/510135366&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>Deep-Time Construction participant Leila Weefur in conversation with curator Gelare Khoshgozaran to discuss their practices in relation to the exhibition.<br><br>More information on the exhibition <a href=\"/gallery/contemptorary-deep-time-construction-2018\" target = \'new\'>here</a>',''),(831,1,'2019-12-15 17:20:32','2020-01-30 21:45:01',64,'PUBLIC EVENT: Vincent Fecteau and Kathy Butterly',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-vincent-fecteau-and-kathy-butterly',NULL,'2019-09-25 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'This event brings together two artists, two exhibitions, and two approaches to making sculpture. In a conversation moderated by Dan Nadel, <a href=\"/gallery/vincent-fecteau-2019\">Vincent Fecteau</a> and Kathy Butterly discuss their work in the context of Fecteau\'s current exhibition at the Wattis and Butterly\'s exhibition at Jan Shrem and Maria Manetti Shrem Museum of Art at UC Davis.<br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/365882010?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>Vincent Fecteau\'s <a href=\"/gallery/vincent-fecteau-2019\">solo exhibition</a> took place in 2019. Click <a href=\"/gallery/vincent-fecteau-2019\">here</a> for images and more information. <br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/wednesday-september-25-2019\">here</a>.',''),(832,1,'2019-12-15 17:22:34','2020-02-01 04:01:58',63,'PUBLIC EVENT: Ute Meta Bauer on Trinh T. Minh-ha',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-ute-meta-bauer-on-trinh-t-minh-ha',NULL,'2019-09-24 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'Curator Ute Meta Bauer presents a talk and conversation on the ways Trinh T. Minh-ha’s thinking, writing, filming, and editing inform and influence each other. Bauer introduces Trinh’s cinematic oeuvre and its habitation in a multiplicity of spaces: of language, translation and passage, longing, and culture.<br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/367136621?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>This is the first event in our year-long season dedicated to the questions posed by the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/trinh-t-minh-ha-is-on-our-mind-2019-2020\">Trinh T. Minh-ha</a> and how they address art, culture, and society today.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/tuesday-september-24-2019\">here</a>.',''),(833,1,'2019-12-15 17:24:43','2020-01-30 21:46:06',62,'PUBLIC EVENT: Fanny Singer on Vincent Fecteau',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-fanny-singer-on-vincent-fecteau',NULL,'2019-09-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/359423962?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>In this lecture, <a href=\"/calendar/saturday-september-7-2019\">Fanny Singer</a> responds to <a href=\"/gallery/vincent-fecteau-2019\">Vincent Fecteau</a>\'s newest body of work. Using their related but different forms and unique finishes as a starting point for a discussion of process, the artist’s references, and the audience’s many potential inferences.<br><br>Vincent Fecteau\'s <a href=\"/gallery/vincent-fecteau-2019\">solo exhibition</a> took place in 2019. Click <a href=\"/gallery/vincent-fecteau-2019\">here</a> for images and more information. <br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/saturday-september-7-2019\">here</a>.',''),(834,1,'2019-12-15 17:29:36','2020-01-30 21:51:02',59,'PUBLIC EVENT: A lecture by Jack Halberstam',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-a-lecture-by-jack-halberstam',NULL,'2019-07-18 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'In this talk, <a href=\"https://english.columbia.edu/content/jack-halberstam\">Jack Halberstam</a> plots yet another history of trans* bodies, one that can be traced through decades of art work and that offers a visual survey of the instability and illegibility that many trans* bodies represent and to which they deliberately cleave.<br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/351014156?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>Jack Halberstam is a professor in the Department of English and Comparative Literature and the Institute for Research on Women, Gender, and Sexuality at Columbia University. <br><br>This is the eleventh event in our year-long season dedicated to themes and questions posed by the work of  <a href=\"/on-our-mind/dodie-bellamy-is-on-our-mind-2018-2019\">Dodie Bellamy</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/thursday-july-18-2019\">here</a>.',''),(835,1,'2019-12-15 17:31:50','2020-02-01 03:56:19',58,'PUBLIC EVENT: Talking Shit: Bluster, Bluff, Braggadocio, and a Poetics of Illegibility, a lecture by Tonya Foster',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-talking-shit-bluster-bluff-braggadocio-and-a-poetics-of-illegibility-a-lecture-by-tonya-foster',NULL,'2019-05-23 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'In this lecture, <a href=\"/calendar/thursday-may-23-2019\">Tonya Foster</a> explores scat-singing as an exemplary process of talking shit, a form of place-making, a performance and deformation of the “authentic,” and more.<br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/341874827?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>Tonya Foster is is the author of the bilingual chapbook <i>La Grammaire des Os</i> and the poetry collection <i>A Swarm of Bees in High Court</i>. A coeditor of <i>Third Mind: Creative Writing through Visual Art</i>, Foster has had work published in <i>Best American Experimental Writing</i> (2016), <i>boundary2, Litscapes: Collected US Writings </i>(2015), <i>MiPoesias, Western Humanities Review, the Hat</i>, and elsewhere.<br><br>This is the tenth event in our year-long season dedicated to themes and questions posed by the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/dodie-bellamy-is-on-our-mind-2018-2019\">Dodie Bellamy</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/thursday-may-23-2019\">here</a>.',''),(836,1,'2019-12-15 17:34:37','2020-02-01 03:55:04',55,'PUBLIC EVENT: A reading and conversation with Pamela M. Lee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-a-reading-and-conversation-with-pamela-m-lee',NULL,'2019-04-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'Art historian <a href=\"https://arthistory.yale.edu/people/pamela-lee\">Pamela M. Lee</a> reads from her work of experimental art criticism, <i>The Glen Park Library</i>,  a “fairy tale” in which Lee argues that the notion of “disruptive” technology in contemporary culture has radically affected our relationship to knowledge, history, language, aesthetics, reading, and truth. <br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/341643058?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>The reading is followed by a conversation with Apsara DiQuinzio, curator of Modern and Contemporary Art at Berkeley Museum of Art and Pacific Film Archive.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/saturday-april-20-2019\">here</a>.',''),(837,1,'2019-12-15 17:36:32','2020-01-30 05:09:41',54,'PUBLIC EVENT: A night of stand-up comedy hosted by Tara Jepsen and Michelle Tea',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-a-night-of-stand-up-comedy-hosted-by-tara-jepsen-and-michelle-tea',NULL,'2019-04-11 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<a href=\"http://www.tarajepsen.com/\">Tara Jepsen</a> and <a href=\"http://www.michelletea.com/\">Michelle Tea</a> are co-hosts of JOSH, a roving stand-up comedy show that takes places in private homes around Los Angeles. JOSH is jokes for people who are often the butt of jokes, centering comedy by women, queers, and people of color.<br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/341652955?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>This is the ninth event in our year-long season dedicated to themes and questions posed by the work of a href=\"/on-our-mind/dodie-bellamy-is-on-our-mind-2018-2019\">Dodie Bellamy</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/thursday-april-11-2019\">here</a>.',''),(838,1,'2019-12-15 17:38:03','2020-01-30 21:50:23',53,'PUBLIC EVENT: A performance by Young Joon Kwak and Kim Ye',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-a-performance-by-young-joon-kwak-and-kim-ye',NULL,'2019-03-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'The multidisciplinary artists <a href=\"https://www.youngjoon.com/\">Young Joon Kwak</a> and <a href=\"https://kimye.com/\">Kim Ye</a> reprise their roles as Mommy and Baby in a live performance. Enacting an initiation into a stereotypical womanhood and destructive femininity, Ye draws on her history as a professional dominatrix to embody an overbearing maternal figure to Kwak’s young daughter. <br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/328257424?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>This is the eighth event in our year-long season dedicated to themes and questions posed by the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/dodie-bellamy-is-on-our-mind-2018-2019\">Dodie Bellamy</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/thursday-march-7-2019\">here</a>.',''),(839,1,'2019-12-15 17:39:41','2020-01-30 21:50:17',52,'PUBLIC EVENT: On Cults, Communes, and Collectives: Launch of Apricota Issue #2 with Joanna Fiduccia, Jennifer Nelson, and Carmen Winant',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'public-event-on-cults-communes-and-collectives-launch-of-apricota-issue-2-with-joanna-fiduccia-jennifer-nelson-and-carmen-winant',NULL,'2019-02-23 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<a href=\"/calendar/saturday-february-23-2019\">Apricota</a> is a journal of modern and contemporary art history and criticism. To launch issue 2, on \"Cults, Communes, and Collectives,\" are presentations by the artist Carmen Winant and the art historian Jennifer Nelson, followed by a conversation with co-editor Joanna Fiduccia. <br><br><div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/320839768?title=0&byline=0&portrait=0\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>This is the seventh event in our year-long season dedicated to themes and questions posed by the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/dodie-bellamy-is-on-our-mind-2018-2019\">Dodie Bellamy</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/saturday-february-23-2019\">here</a>.',''),(840,1,'2019-12-16 14:15:16','2020-01-30 21:51:22',65,'PUBLIC EVENT: Lecture by Trinh T. Minh-ha',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'840',NULL,'2019-11-07 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary 'In this talk, <a href=\"/on-our-mind/trinh-t-minh-ha-is-on-our-mind-2019-2020/about-trinh-t-minh-ha\">Trinh T. Minh-ha</a> focuses on “Voice” as an activity by which the text’s social, ethical, and aesthetic positioning is conveyed to the reader/viewer.<br><br><iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/715988725&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>This is the third event in our year-long season dedicated to the questions posed by the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/trinh-t-minh-ha-is-on-our-mind-2019-2020/about-trinh-t-minh-ha\">Trinh T. Minh-ha</a> and how they address art, culture, and society today.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\"/calendar/thursday-november-7-2019\">here</a>.',''),(841,1,'2019-12-16 18:53:15','2020-01-30 01:55:20',NULL,'Dodie Bellamy Institute:Â Readings by Linda Bakke,Â Michele Carlson,Â Victoria Gannon,Â Carlos Jackson,Â and Ismail Muhammad',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'dodie-bellamy-institute-a-readings-by-linda-bakke-a-michele-carlson-a-victoria-gannon-a-carlos-jackson-a-and-ismail-muhammad',NULL,'2018-10-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/525228339&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>Linda Bakke, Michele Carlson, Victoria Gannon, Carlos Jackson, and Ismail Muhammad, all former students of Dodie Bellamy, read their work, and, by extension, provide an introduction to a new generations of Bay Area writers and poets.<br><br>This is the third event in our year-long season dedicated to the questions posed by the work of Dodie Bellamy and how they address art, culture, and society today.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/friday-october-26-2018\'>here</a> .<br>',''),(842,1,'2019-12-16 18:54:15','2020-01-30 02:02:44',NULL,'Dodie Bellamy Institute: Andrew Durbin on Dodie Bellamy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'dodie-bellamy-institute-andrew-durbin-on-dodie-bellamy',NULL,'2018-09-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/503339883&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>Lecture by Andrew Durbin on Dodie Bellamy. Durbin is an American poet and novelist, and an avid reader of Bellamy\'s work, along with the work of other writers from the New Narrative movement of the 1970s and 80s. Like them, he sees autobiography as something to use, but also to subvert, pervert, and perform.<br><br>This is the first event in our year-long season dedicated to the questions posed by the work of <a href=\'/on-our-mind/dodie-bellamy-is-on-our-mind-2018-2019\'>Dodie Bellamy</a> and how they address art, culture, and society today.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/thursday-september-20-2018\'>here</a> <br><br>',''),(843,1,'2019-12-16 18:55:16','2020-01-30 03:40:32',NULL,'Seth Price Institute:Â Sheila Heti with Ross Simonini',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'seth-price-institute-a-sheila-heti-with-ross-simonini',NULL,'2018-05-08 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/448779192&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>The Canadian author Sheila Heti discusses and launches her new book, as well as the broader questions around the genre of autofiction today, with the artist and writer Ross Simonini.<br><br>This is the ninth event in our <a href=\'/on-our-mind/seth-price-is-on-our-mind-2017-2018\'>year-long</a> season about and around the work of Seth Price.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/tuesday-may-8-2018\'>here</a> <br><br><br>',''),(844,1,'2019-12-16 18:56:15','2019-12-16 18:56:29',NULL,'Seth Price Institute:Â James Fei performs \"I am Sitting in a Room\"Â (A.Â Lucier)Â and \"The Nerve Meter\"Â (J.Â Fei)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'seth-price-institute-a-james-fei-performs-i-am-sitting-in-a-room-a-a-a-lucier-a-and-the-nerve-meter-a-j-a-fei',NULL,'2018-04-26 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/448775544&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe>',''),(845,1,'2019-12-16 18:57:21','2020-01-30 03:52:46',NULL,'Seth Price Institute: An evening with Seth Price and Sohrab Mohebbi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'seth-price-institute-an-evening-with-seth-price-and-sohrab-mohebbi',NULL,'2018-02-23 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/422506464&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>Curator Sohrab Mohebbi and Seth Price are in conversation with each other and with the audience. <br><br>This is the sixth event in our year-long season about and around the work of <a href=\'/on-our-mind/seth-price-is-on-our-mind-2017-2018\'>Seth Price</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/friday-february-23-2018\'>here</a> <br>',''),(846,1,'2019-12-16 18:58:28','2020-02-01 04:43:35',NULL,'Seth Price Institute:Â Sun-ha Hong on data,Â or on turning bodies into facts',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'seth-price-institute-a-sun-ha-hong-on-data-a-or-on-turning-bodies-into-facts',NULL,'2018-03-20 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/421958388&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>For Sun-ha Hong, the promise of data is the promise to turn bodies into facts: emotions, behavior, and every messy amorphous human reality can be distilled into the discrete, clean cuts of calculable information. <br><br>This is the seventh event in our year-long season about and around the work of <a href=\'/on-our-mind/seth-price-is-on-our-mind-2017-2018\'>Seth Price</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/tuesday-march-20-2018\'>here</a> <br><br>',''),(847,1,'2019-12-16 18:59:27','2020-01-30 04:10:55',NULL,'Michele Carlson: a reading in response to Mechanisms',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'michele-carlson-a-reading-in-response-to-mechanisms',NULL,'2018-02-15 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/407802339&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>Artist, writer, and curator Michele Carlson presents a reading in response to the exhibition, <a href=\"/gallery/mechanisms-2017-18\"><i>Mechanisms</i> </a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/thursday-february-15-2018\'>here</a> ',''),(848,1,'2019-12-16 19:00:24','2020-01-30 04:23:51',NULL,'Seth Price Institute:Â Andrew Culp on the aesthetics of refusal',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'seth-price-institute-a-andrew-culp-on-the-aesthetics-of-refusal',NULL,'2018-01-18 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/391404069&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe><br><br>In this lecture on the aesthetics of refusal, philosopher Andrew Culp extends anarchism into politics: <i>the lesson to be drawn is that negation is finding a way to say “no” to those who tell us to take the world as it is</i>.<br><br>This is the fifth event in our year-long season about and around the work of <a href=\'/on-our-mind/seth-price-is-on-our-mind-2017-2018\'>Seth Price</a>.<br><br>More information on the event is <a href=\'/calendar/thursday-january-18-2018\'>here</a> <br><br><br> ',''),(849,1,'2019-12-16 19:01:45','2019-12-16 19:01:59',NULL,'Jennifer Alexander: The Mantra of Efficiency',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'jennifer-alexander-the-mantra-of-efficiency',NULL,'2017-10-17 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/355258106&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe>',''),(850,1,'2019-12-16 19:02:41','2019-12-16 19:02:56',NULL,'Seth Price Institute: Michelle Kuo on Seth Price',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'seth-price-institute-michelle-kuo-on-seth-price',NULL,'2017-09-16 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/343458590&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe>',''),(851,1,'2019-12-16 19:03:37','2020-01-30 01:35:37',NULL,'David Hammons Institute:Â Tongo Eisen-Martin and friends',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'david-hammons-institute-a-tongo-eisen-martin-and-friends',NULL,'2017-02-21 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<div style=\"padding:56.25% 0 0 0;position:relative;\"><iframe src=\"https://vimeo.com/214249463\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"autoplay; fullscreen\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div><script src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/api/player.js\"></script><br><br>San Francisco poet Tongo Eisen-Martin brings together his community of peers for an evening of poetry and performance. This event features performances by poets Josiah Alderete, Tongo Eisen-Martin, Raina Leon, and Andrea Murphy, and music by Lewis Jordan and Akinyele Sadiq.<br><br>This is an event in our year-long season dedicated to themes and questions posed by the work of <a href=\"/on-our-mind/david-hammons-is-on-our-mind-2016-2017\">David Hammons</a>.<br><br>More information on the event <a href=\"/calendar/tuesday-february-21-2017\">here</a>.<br>',''),(852,1,'2019-12-16 19:04:33','2019-12-16 19:04:48',NULL,'David Hammons Institute:Â Fred Moten on Ralph Ellison\'s Invisible Man',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'david-hammons-institute-a-fred-moten-on-ralph-ellison-s-invisible-man',NULL,'2017-03-10 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/317707480&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&hide_related=true&show_comments=false&show_user=false&show_reposts=false&show_teaser=false&visual=false\"></iframe>',''),(853,1,'2019-12-16 19:05:37','2019-12-16 19:05:53',NULL,'David Hammons Institute:Â Lawrence \"Butch\" Morris screening,Â with Zeena Parkins',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'david-hammons-institute-a-lawrence-butch-morris-screening-a-with-zeena-parkins',NULL,'2016-12-15 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,'',_binary '<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"no\" allow=\"autoplay\" src=\"https://w.soundcloud.com/player/?url=https%3A//api.soundcloud.com/tracks/317714899&color=%23000000&auto_play=false&